# Deploy package versioning

Deployable surfaces version **independently** in each `package.json`:

`apps/api` · `apps/worker` · `apps/web` · `apps/marketing` · `apps/admin`

Shared libs (`config`, `db`, `db-admin`, `types`, `utils`, `github-app-auth`, `ui`) stay at `0.0.0` — consumer bumps required.

## When to bump

Before `git push` to `staging` or `main` — not on every commit.

```bash
pnpm setup:hooks
pnpm bump:versions
git add apps/*/package.json
git commit -m "chore(repo)[#N]: bump versions for push"
# full CI gate, then push
```

## Shared-lib → consumer map

| Shared package | Bump these deployables |
|---|---|
| `packages/config` | api, worker, web, marketing, admin |
| `packages/db` | api, worker |
| `packages/db-admin` | admin |
| `packages/types` | api, worker, web |
| `packages/utils` | api, worker, web, admin |
| `packages/github-app-auth` | api, worker, admin |
| `packages/ui` | web, marketing, admin |

Locale JSON under `apps/web/src/i18n/` and `apps/marketing/` **requires** a version bump — not in the policy ignore list.

## Agent obligations

When pushing deployable code: bump versions → full CI gate → push. Pre-push hook validates semver increased when deploy-relevant source changed.

Skip once: `SKIP_DEPLOY_VERSION_BUMP_CHECK=1 git push --no-verify`

Manual check: `pnpm check:push-version-bumps`

Dry-run bumps: `pnpm bump:versions --dry-run`

Force bump all: `pnpm bump:versions:force`
